modules.name: Data.Decimal
modules.comments: This module defines a `Decimal` data type for arbitrary precision numbers.

declarations.comments:
Parse a string into a `Decimal`, assuming a decimal representation. Returns
`Nothing` if the parse fails.

Examples:
```purescript
fromString "42.001"
fromString "857981209301293808359384092830482"
fromString "1e100"
fromString "0.12301928309128183579487598149533"
```
declarations.title: fromString

declarations.comments: Convert an integer to a Decimal.
declarations.title: fromInt

declarations.comments: Convert a number to a Decimal.
declarations.title: fromNumber

declarations.comments: Converts a Decimal to a Number, possibly resulting in loss of precision.
declarations.title: toNumber

declarations.comments: A representation of the `Decimal` as a `String`.
declarations.title: toString

declarations.comments:
A representation of the `Decimal` as a `String`, rounded to the given
number of significant digits
declarations.title: toPrecision

declarations.comments:
A representation of the `Decimal` as a `String` in fixed-point notation
rounded to the given number of decimal places. Never returns exponential
notation. Uses the default rounding mode.
declarations.title: toFixed

declarations.comments:
Returns true if the value of this `Decimal` is a finite number (not
infinite, not `NaN`).
declarations.title: isFinite

declarations.comments: Returns true if the value of this `Decimal` is a whole number.
declarations.title: isInteger

declarations.comments: Round to the given number of significant digits.
declarations.title: toSignificantDigits
